Subject: [PATCH 1/2] x86, cpu: Add cpufeature flag for PCIDs
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Patch-mainline: v3.2
Git-commit: be604e695f9a0db4cd5c4c232857a10c6bc9dee4
References: fate#313826

This patch add a flag for Process-Context Identifiers (PCIDs) aka
Address Space Identifiers (ASIDs) aka Tagged TLB support.

Signed-off-by: Arun Thomas <arun.thomas@gmail.com>
Link: http://lkml.kernel.org/r/1313782943-3898-1-git-send-email-arun.thomas@gmail.com
Acked-by: Suresh Siddha <suresh.b.siddha@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: H. Peter Anvin <hpa@linux.intel.com>
(cherry picked from commit be604e695f9a0db4cd5c4c232857a10c6bc9dee4)

Signed-off-by: Andreas Färber <afaerber@suse.de>
---
 arch/x86/include/asm/cpufeature.h |    1 +
 1 Datei geändert, 1 Zeile hinzugefügt(+)

diff --git a/arch/x86/include/asm/cpufeature.h b/arch/x86/include/asm/cpufeature.h
index 00533f6..06ac811 100644
--- a/arch/x86/include/asm/cpufeature.h
+++ b/arch/x86/include/asm/cpufeature.h
@@ -114,6 +114,7 @@
 #define X86_FEATURE_CX16	(4*32+13) /* CMPXCHG16B */
 #define X86_FEATURE_XTPR	(4*32+14) /* Send Task Priority Messages */
 #define X86_FEATURE_PDCM	(4*32+15) /* Performance Capabilities */
+#define X86_FEATURE_PCID	(4*32+17) /* Process Context Identifiers */
 #define X86_FEATURE_DCA		(4*32+18) /* Direct Cache Access */
 #define X86_FEATURE_XMM4_1	(4*32+19) /* "sse4_1" SSE-4.1 */
 #define X86_FEATURE_XMM4_2	(4*32+20) /* "sse4_2" SSE-4.2 */
